WEBVTT

00:41.083 --> 00:43.620
<i>My name is Wesley Deeds the Third.</i>

00:45.587 --> 00:48.921
<i>I grew up fifth generation
Ivy League graduate.</i>

00:49.967 --> 00:52.129
<i>I can tell you my pedigree
all the way back to the tribe</i>

00:52.219 --> 00:54.551
<i>that my greatest grandfather came from.</i>

00:55.806 --> 00:57.513
<i>I was born into privilege,</i>

00:57.599 --> 01:00.182
<i>groomed by my father to be a businessman,</i>

01:00.269 --> 01:02.226
<i>to take over his company.</i>

01:02.312 --> 01:05.850
<i>Groomed by my mother to be a gentleman.</i>

01:05.941 --> 01:08.478
<i>I was told where to stand and how to dress,</i>

01:08.819 --> 01:10.435
<i>how to cut my hair,</i>

01:10.529 --> 01:12.395
<i>and what I would be doing
for the rest of my life</i>

01:12.489 --> 01:15.607
<i>from the time that I was five years old.</i>

01:15.701 --> 01:18.864
<i>And right now, I seem to be on track.</i>

01:18.954 --> 01:20.285
<i>Whose track, I don't really know.</i>

01:22.165 --> 01:24.122
<i>By this time,
my mother thought I should be married,</i>

01:24.876 --> 01:29.461
<i>and according to my life schedule,
it's four months</i> away.

01:29.590 --> 01:32.799
<i>I'll be marrying her, Natalie.</i>

01:32.884 --> 01:34.795
<i>She's amazing.</i>

01:34.886 --> 01:38.220
<i>We're perfect together.</i>

01:38.307 --> 01:41.800
<i>With</i> a <i>life like mine,
you'd think that I wake up happy every day,</i>

01:41.893 --> 01:43.850
<i>but I don't.</i>

01:43.937 --> 01:45.974
<i>My life is perfect.</i>

01:46.064 --> 01:49.853
<i>But I often wonder, am I living my own life,</i>

01:49.943 --> 01:52.731
<i>or the life that I've been told to live?</i>

01:56.408 --> 01:58.695
This tie is too dark.

02:03.040 --> 02:05.247
I think this tie is too dark.

02:06.668 --> 02:07.874
Green.

02:08.669 --> 02:11.037
Green. Green's better.

02:18.263 --> 02:22.427
Maria forgot to put the shoe stretchers
in my shoes.

02:28.106 --> 02:30.768
Babe, you know Maria forgot to
put my shoe stretchers in again?

02:30.859 --> 02:32.816
- Really?
- Yeah.

02:32.903 --> 02:34.769
I'll talk to her.

02:34.863 --> 02:36.854
<i>I'll tell you who it won't be,
Deeds Incorporated.</i>

02:36.948 --> 02:39.280
<i>According to the rumor mill,
the software giant...</i>

02:39.993 --> 02:42.530
No, I've been listening to the radio.

02:44.373 --> 02:45.738
Yeah.

02:45.832 --> 02:48.244
No,no,no.
Listen, this is what I want you to do.

02:48.335 --> 02:51.578
Just get everybody, set up a conference call,

02:51.672 --> 02:54.255
I will figure it out when I get there.

02:54.341 --> 02:56.753
John, don't panic. It's all fine.

02:56.843 --> 02:59.335
I'm looking at the paper now.

02:59.429 --> 03:01.295
Okay. Thanks.

03:01.390 --> 03:02.380
Hello.

03:02.808 --> 03:04.640
Yeah, I have a morning meeting.

03:04.726 --> 03:07.388
Showing the Jones apartment. Right.

03:07.479 --> 03:10.813
Hey, can you tell Jeffrey
to have something cool for kids?

03:11.441 --> 03:13.557
