to build this business,

18:02.665 --> 18:04.906
and to lose it like this would be unthinkable.

18:05.251 --> 18:08.960
Don't worry, Mom, perfect little Wesley's
gonna work it all out for you.

18:09.171 --> 18:11.412
Oh, yes, he will.

18:11.507 --> 18:14.625
And you will find some way
to try to sabotage it.

18:14.927 --> 18:16.713
Where are you going?

18:16.804 --> 18:19.762
I'm going to have a cigarette. Is that okay?

18:20.558 --> 18:22.094
I can't drive.

18:23.185 --> 18:24.220
Wesley has to drive me, Mom,

18:24.312 --> 18:27.145
'cause you have my car locked up
in the office garage.

18:27.732 --> 18:30.190
Okay? I'm going to have a smoke.

18:34.655 --> 18:37.738
It takes the patience of Job to deal with him.

18:40.077 --> 18:43.991
Don't get worked up about it, Mother.
He's fine. It's all fine.

19:06.020 --> 19:07.556
Okay, go on.

19:18.532 --> 19:20.318
Now listen.

19:20.409 --> 19:24.448
I need you to help Mommy and be a big girl.

19:24.538 --> 19:27.326
- You can lay down...
- I'm scared.

19:27.416 --> 19:32.252
No, listen, you can try and go to sleep,
and I'll be back to check on you in an hour.

19:32.338 --> 19:34.170
I want Daddy.

19:34.256 --> 19:37.248
Ariel, don't do that.

19:37.343 --> 19:39.550
Don't do that "Daddy" thing.

19:39.637 --> 19:41.048
Come on.

19:45.893 --> 19:50.137
But you must not come out of the closet,
all right?

19:50.231 --> 19:53.189
And I'll be back to check on you in an hour.

20:05.788 --> 20:07.529
Put the participation
and the operating profit,

20:07.623 --> 20:08.988
and you take that from the gross...

20:09.083 --> 20:11.324
I don't understand what he's doing,
or how he's doing this.

20:11.419 --> 20:13.831
- Can we go home now?
- What?

20:14.630 --> 20:16.416
Can we go home now?

20:18.467 --> 20:20.583
I'm still working, Walter.

20:20.678 --> 20:22.760
And you should be, too.
Did you finish the Brunson report?

20:26.559 --> 20:28.596
Anything else, Mr. CEO?

20:33.816 --> 20:35.022
I'm taking a cab home.

20:38.821 --> 20:40.562
Don't say a word.

20:42.283 --> 20:44.820
You know, everybody around here
is talking about him, it's not just me.

20:45.035 --> 20:48.403
He's not doing a very good job.
He's sleeping with several staffers.

20:48.497 --> 20:50.204
John. My brother.

20:51.167 --> 20:53.579
My father told me to take care of him
and that's what I intend to do.

20:53.669 --> 20:55.501
Can you take care of this, please?
Make sure it's right.

20:57.423 --> 20:59.039
Okay. Look, I gotta go.

20:59.133 --> 21:01.750
Heidi's going out with Natalie tonight
and I get to play Daddy.

21:02.386 --> 21:03.501
Okay.

21:04.680 --> 21:06.717
Come on. Let's do this tomorrow morning.

21:06.807 --> 21:09.048
No, no, I'm not leaving here
until I figure this out.

21:09.143 --> 21:12.261
This one, I'm gonna burn the midnight oil.
Something's up.

21:12.605 --> 21:14.721
All right. I'll talk to you later.

21:14.815 --> 21:17.022
All right, yeah.

21:17.109 --> 21:19.316
- Tell Heidi I said hi.
- Yeah.

21:24.158 --> 21:27.651
Okay, John, okay. I love you.
Kiss the kids for me, okay?

21:27.745 --> 21:29.736
All right. Bye, I love you.

21:29.830 --> 21:32.071
How amazing is it
that he's given me tonight off?

21:32.166 --> 21:33.622
I mean, I can't believe it, we're out!

21:33.709 --> 21:35.325
Yeah, I'm so glad you could come out, girl.

21:35.419 --> 21:39.504
Me, too! I know, the kids keep me so busy.

21:39.590 --> 21:41.297
Okay, Heidi, can we please not talk
about your kids today?

21:41.383 --> 21:42.589
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

21:42.676 --> 21:46.044
You know what? I'm sorry. I'm a jerk.

21:46.138 --> 21:48.926
It's just that all we ever talk about
these days are your kids.

21:49.016 --> 21:53.226
I know, I'm sorry. It's girls' night out.

21:53.312 --> 21:55.929
So we're here for Mark.
No kids, no husbands.

21:56.106 --> 21:59.519
No future husbands.
In fact, I am turning this phone off.

21:59.610 --> 22:02.193
Thank you.

22:02.279 --> 22:04.395
- So how late we gonna be out tonight?
- As late as we wanna be.

22:04.490 --> 22:08.950
Okay. Better call the nanny and tell her... No.

22:09.036 --> 22:13.030
You better call Wesley
and tell him it's gonna be a long night.

22:13.123 --> 22:17.833
No,no,no.
We do not have that kind of relationship.

22:17.920 --> 22:22.130
- What do you mean?
- We just don't check in with each other.

22:22.216 --> 22:25.334
- You don't?
- No.

22:25.427 --> 22:29.170
- What?
- I just don't understand that.

22:29.265 --> 22:34.760
No, I don't have to check in with him,
because I know where he is.

22:34.854 --> 22:36.970
I can literally set my watch by Wesley.

22:37.064 --> 22:39.180
Like, he always does the same thing,

22:39.275 --> 22:43.143
and he's always gonna do the same thing,
so...

22:43.237 --> 22:48.152
Like right now,
I know that he's working late in his office.

22:48.242 --> 22:49.732
Wow.

22:49.827 --> 22:52.239
- What? What?
- It's just crazy.

23:41.378 --> 23:42.709
<i>- Hello?
- John.</i>

23:42.796 --> 23:45.834
Hey, listen, I am sitting at the office,

23:45.925 --> 23:48.041
and I've gone through
all of these financial reports,

23:48.135 --> 23:49.921
-and I see what Brunson is doing.
- What?

23:50.012 --> 23:51.173
He's in dire straits.

23:51.263 --> 23:54.221
He has got this other company
that is interested in bidding,

23:54.308 --> 23:56.174
so he's trying to drive up all of his prices.

23:56.268 --> 23:58.805
That's why
he took the biggest client from us.

23:58.896 --> 24:01.684
It is pretty evident
he can't afford to support him.

24:02.441 --> 24:04.102
<i>You sound pretty sure about this.</i>

24:04.193 --> 24:07.060
I know it, man.
I'm sitting here, I'm looking at it.

24:07.154 --> 24:10.397
It's pretty clever, but I knew I'd find it.

24:10.491 --> 24:13.108
You know what, can you try and get
a meeting with him for me tomorrow?

24:13.202 --> 24:14.818
<i>Yeah, okay.
I'll call him first thing in the morning.</i>

24:27.049 --> 24:29.837
This is a message for Ms. James.

24:29.927 --> 24:32.009
It's Lindsey Wakefield.

24:32.096 --> 24:35.589
I need to talk to you about making
some kind of payment arrangements,

24:35.683 --> 24:40.849
and I will call you at 10:00 a.m.
sharp tomorrow.

24:40.938 --> 24:44.272
I'll be working,
so that's the only time I can call...

24:44.358 --> 24:45.644
Bye.

24:47.861 --> 24:49.147
I'm sorry.

24:49.238 --> 24:52.276
I didn't know that anybody was here.

24:52.366 --> 24:55.575
You do know
that's grounds for termination, right?

24:57.371 --> 25:00.864
You gonna run off,
tell massa everything what's goin' on?

25:01.125 --> 25:03.457
Just give me a break, black man.

25:11.844 --> 25:13.005
"Run tell massa"?

25:15.055 --> 25:18.138
I know about the old white dude
that owns this place.

25:18.225 --> 25:21.138
He's evil to all you employees. Look, I get it.

25:21.228 --> 25:22.559
I won't do it again.

25:23.147 --> 25:26.890
Old white dude. What's his name?

25:27.276 --> 25:30.644
I don't know. You don't know his...

25:30.738 --> 25:33.856
Deeds? Deeds Incorporated?

25:34.199 --> 25:36.782
It doesn't matter.
I'm not gonna use the phone again.

25:36.869 --> 25:38.030
MASS-ll

25:41.081 --> 25:44.199
You think you gonna get some ass
to keep your mouth shut?

25:44.293 --> 25:45.408
What is wrong with you?

25:45.502 --> 25:49.291
Lady, I wasn't asking for ass.

25:49.381 --> 25:51.839
You called me an ass,

25:52.885 --> 25:55.001
when you parked in my spot.

25:56.638 --> 25:59.005
Yes, that was me. I'm so sorry.

25:59.099 --> 26:01.841
I really need this job.
I'm in all kinds of... Please.

26:01.935 --> 26:06.179
When I saw your child sitting in that car,
she was afraid.

26:06.690 --> 26:10.934
Reminded me of the time that my parents
took me to the Maldives one summer.

26:11.278 --> 26:15.067
My father said, "Don't go into the sea, son.
I can't swim, so don't go in."

26:15.157 --> 26:19.947
I didn't care. I grabbed the life ring,
soon as he turned his back ljumped in.

26:21.455 --> 26:23.867
I almost drowned.

26:23.957 --> 26:27.541
My father's standing there,
screaming, "Swim, son, swim!"

26:28.837 --> 26:31.955
Children don't really know
what adults know.

26:33.133 --> 26:37.548
You shouldn't leave her alone in a car.
And don't use the phone again.

26:37.638 --> 26:39.629
How many kids you got?

26:42.476 --> 26:44.592
How many kids have you got?

26:45.312 --> 26:46.802
I don't have any children.

26:47.564 --> 26:49.726
Yeah. That's what I thought.

26:50.567 --> 26:53.810
So don't you lecture me
on how to raise my child,

26:55.155 --> 26:56.737
Mr. Maldives.

27:04.706 --> 27:05.696
How'd you get out?

27:09.670 --> 27:10.831
Excuse me?

27:12.339 --> 27:16.003
The water. Your daddy couldn't swim,
so how'd you get out?

27:17.427 --> 27:20.340
My brother. He jumped in and saved me.

27:22.349 --> 27:25.341
See, you should've kept your ass
on the shore.

27:57.843 --> 27:59.004
What?

28:04.391 --> 28:05.973
Are you following me?

28:08.103 --> 28:09.389
Where'd you come from, beautiful?

28:09.730 --> 28:11.437
The babysitterjust dropped her off.

28:11.523 --> 28:14.356
Ariel, can you get down from there?

28:14.443 --> 28:16.684
You know, you really shouldn't be
sitting here on these side streets.

28:16.778 --> 28:19.110
My secretary got mugged
going to her car one night. Pretty...

28:19.656 --> 28:21.021
Thank you!

28:46.391 --> 28:48.348
What? What do you want?

28:52.689 --> 28:53.895
Are you okay?

28:55.776 --> 28:57.517
I was gonna ask you the same thing.
Are you okay?

28:57.611 --> 28:59.648
You're just sitting here.

29:01.281 --> 29:05.525
My car won't start, but it's fine.

29:06.119 --> 29:09.703
I don't know much about cars, but I could
call a tow truck for you, maybe.

29:10.624 --> 29:13.082
Yeah, you did that already.

29:13.627 --> 29:16.210
I don't mind dropping you and your
daughter off somewhere if you like.

29:16.755 --> 29:22.250
No, I have a friend
who's gonna be here soon.

29:22.636 --> 29:24.047
- Somebody's on their way?
- Yeah.

29:24.137 --> 29:26.344
- Okay, I'll just wait, then.
- No! What?

29:26.431 --> 29:27.592
I'll just find a spot here.

29:30.435 --> 29:32.642
He is not gonna park his car.

29:35.315 --> 29:36.476
He is gonna...

29:42.114 --> 29:45.197
Ariel, just keep quiet, all right?

29:49.496 --> 29:51.954
I don't know what this man wants.

29:59.548 --> 30:01.539
But...

30:01.633 --> 30:03.169
I did not invite you in my car.

30:04.511 --> 30:05.672
Hi.

30:07.180 --> 30:08.261
What's your name?

30:08.348 --> 30:10.089
- Ariel.
- I'm Wesley.

30:12.144 --> 30:13.600
You know Ariel's the name of a mermaid?

30:13.687 --> 30:14.768
Did anybody tell you that?

30:14.855 --> 30:16.266
How do you know that?

30:16.940 --> 30:17.930
I know something about it.

30:18.025 --> 30:21.609
I got a friend who has two kids
and they love The <i>Little</i> Mermaid.

30:24.364 --> 30:27.197
- Did you hear my name?
- Well, obviously.

30:28.910 --> 30:32.278
Well, you just told her. It's Wesley. I got it.

30:34.207 --> 30:35.743
Wesley Deeds.

30:39.546 --> 30:40.627
What?

30:41.423 --> 30:43.289
I'm the old white man.

30:52.100 --> 30:53.465
And you are?

30:57.397 --> 31:00.139
- Unemployed, Fight?
- No.

31:00.859 --> 31:03.396
I'm so humiliated. I'm so sorry.

31:06.239 --> 31:08.230
And I called you an ass.

31:09.743 --> 31:11.199
I'm Lindsey.

31:12.245 --> 31:14.486
Good to meet you, Lindsey.

31:14.581 --> 31:17.573
And you don't have to stay here.

31:17.918 --> 31:19.500
It's all good.

31:19.920 --> 31:23.163
No, it's fine, really.
My secretary was mugged.

31:23.256 --> 31:25.748
I felt really bad when she was,
'cause I had her working really late...

31:25.842 --> 31:29.801
- So you want to stay in the car.
- I'll stay here, it's all fine.

31:33.767 --> 31:34.973
You work with my mom?

31:37.104 --> 31:38.435
Yes, I do.

31:38.688 --> 31:41.180
- What floor?
- On the top floor.

31:41.566 --> 31:44.399
- I was on the top.
- No, Ariel, don't...

31:45.153 --> 31:47.565
Don't be bothering Mr. Deeds
with all that chat.

31:48.824 --> 31:50.064
Sorry.

32:02.462 --> 32:04.373
Got a lot of stuff in here.

32:04.631 --> 32:06.121
We...

32:06.883 --> 32:08.965
We're in the process of moving.

32:09.928 --> 32:12.966
Right, baby? We're done. Almost done.

32:13.390 --> 32:14.471
What part of town?

32:14.766 --> 32:16.427
I don't think you'd know it.

32:25.986 --> 32:27.317
Is that your stomach?

32:27.946 --> 32:29.357
Are you hungry?

32:29.448 --> 32:33.362
What? Again?
Sweetie, you didn't eat with the babysitter?

32:35.036 --> 32:37.573
You know, there's a pizza joint
right up the block here.

32:37.664 --> 32:40.281
You want to take a walk?
Would you like some pizza?

32:40.375 --> 32:43.208
No. I don't think I have my wallet.

32:43.295 --> 32:45.912
No, I got it, it's fine. Now come on.

32:46.840 --> 32:48.547
Come on, honey.

32:48.675 --> 32:50.507
Come on, let's go.
It's right around the corner.

32:51.011 --> 32:54.754
- Come on, Ariel!
- Okay, that's what we're doing. Yep.

32:54.848 --> 32:56.680
That's just perfect.

33:20.332 --> 33:22.289
Mark, I think she needs our help.

33:22.375 --> 33:24.616
I need a drink. Is this me?

33:24.711 --> 33:27.669
So, what's going on with you?

33:27.756 --> 33:29.713
What? Why aren't you guys dancing?

33:30.050 --> 33:33.008
- Why have you not stopped dancing?
- Because I'm having a good time.

33:33.094 --> 33:35.085
The last time you did this
was back in college,

33:35.180 --> 33:37.512
-when you broke up with...
- Rene, right!

33:37.891 --> 33:40.883
- What are you guys talking about?
- Why haven't I met your future husband yet?

33:40.977 --> 33:43.264
'Cause you're busy.
He's busy, everybody's busy.

33:43.355 --> 33:47.019
No one is that busy, okay?
I met Rene the first week you met him.

33:47.108 --> 33:49.475
You were in love,
you were falling all over him.

33:49.569 --> 33:52.652
You talked about him all the time.
This man, you do not talk about.

33:53.114 --> 33:56.732
He's amazing, okay?
He's fantastic and I am in love.

33:57.911 --> 34:00.824
- Am I missing something?
- Yes, a good time.

34:00.914 --> 34:03.622
You Debbie Downers are blowing my buzz.

34:10.715 --> 34:11.830
You're really enjoying that, aren't you?

34:12.926 --> 34:14.087
Yeah.

34:17.806 --> 34:20.797
You know, you have eyed that video game

34:20.891 --> 34:22.724
five times in the last four minutes.

34:23.186 --> 34:24.893
Do you want to play?

34:24.980 --> 34:26.469
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

34:27.524 --> 34:31.688
My mom doesn't have enough money
to play fun things.

34:34.114 --> 34:35.980
No, fun things should be free. Come on!

34:37.117 --> 34:39.324
I got a little money, come on.

34:41.454 --> 34:43.320
Do you know how to play this?

34:43.790 --> 34:45.871
Let's see what we got here.

34:47.460 --> 34:48.916
This one? Here we are.

34:49.629 --> 34:50.960
Hey, hey.

35:00.473 --> 35:02.555
She's a pretty special kid.

35:03.184 --> 35:06.472
- Hey, I don't know why she's so hungry.
- Kids are always hungry.

35:10.108 --> 35:11.769
Harley.

35:11.860 --> 35:13.191
- Softail Deluxe.
- Deluxe!

35:13.278 --> 35:14.268
What do you know about it?

35:14.821 --> 35:17.939
Her daddy used to work at a place
called Baker Boy's Bikes.

35:18.158 --> 35:19.648
- On Elm?
- Yes!

35:19.826 --> 35:22.488
- You know it?
- I do, I do.

35:22.579 --> 35:23.569
Well, small world.

35:23.663 --> 35:26.371
I remember when I was a kid,
boy, I would spend hours there all the time.

35:26.541 --> 35:27.576
You ride?

35:27.667 --> 35:31.001
I did once. When I was about 17.

35:33.298 --> 35:35.756
We'd hang out there all day. We all wanted...
It's so crazy.

35:35.842 --> 35:37.879
We all wanted to get Harleys, right?

35:37.969 --> 35:41.132
We just had this dream of riding our bikes

35:41.222 --> 35:43.589
all over the world,
digging wells in remote villages.

35:44.100 --> 35:46.842
So I started trying to learn how to ride

35:46.936 --> 35:51.430
and my mom found out I was hanging out
down there and she hit the roof.

35:51.524 --> 35:52.685
Crazy, right?

35:53.234 --> 35:56.898
I don't think that is crazy at all.
It means you have a good heart.

35:58.365 --> 36:00.356
That's what that means.

36:05.622 --> 36:07.033
So you ride?

36:08.875 --> 36:09.956
You're looking at a pro.

36:10.335 --> 36:13.248
Oh, come on. That I would like to see.

36:13.797 --> 36:15.583
Well, not on this salary, you won't.

36:18.968 --> 36:20.550
So am I fired?

36:23.264 --> 36:24.345
No.

36:25.058 --> 36:27.470
But I gotta tell you,
nobody's ever talked to me like that before.

36:28.561 --> 36:31.428
You park in my spot, you call me an ass.

36:31.523 --> 36:35.733
Shoot, I mean, it's just been
a pretty interesting day, my friend.

36:37.195 --> 36:40.608
- That is sad, if that is true.
- What's sad?

36:40.949 --> 36:42.781
It means nobody's ever told you the truth...

36:42.867 --> 36:44.949
- No, I beg to differ.
-...that's what that means.

36:45.120 --> 36:48.329
People tell me the truth, they're just not...

36:48.415 --> 36:50.076
They're just not rude when they say it.

36:50.166 --> 36:53.659
I wouldn't call it rude.
I was just being direct.

36:53.753 --> 36:54.914
Direct?

36:55.755 --> 36:58.543
- Okay, fine. If you say so.
- I do.

36:58.633 --> 36:59.794
Direct.

37:01.010 --> 37:02.876
Does that turn you on?

37:08.393 --> 37:10.009
- Now you got jokes.
- Look at your face.

37:10.353 --> 37:11.434
Funny, too.

37:14.441 --> 37:17.103
How long have you worked at the company?

37:18.278 --> 37:19.313
A year.

37:21.573 --> 37:25.157
So what is it, this Deeds Incorporated?

37:26.244 --> 37:27.484
What do you do?

37:27.579 --> 37:29.286
My father was a computer whiz.

37:29.873 --> 37:34.413
And he came up with this great software,
sold it to the government.

37:34.502 --> 37:35.708
It was top secret.

37:35.795 --> 37:39.208
About 20 years ago
he got it declassified and went public.

37:39.299 --> 37:41.210
Company went through the roof.

37:41.301 --> 37:45.090
A little help from affirmative action,
because it was very necessary.

37:45.180 --> 37:47.421
From there,
he started buying smaller companies,

37:47.515 --> 37:50.473
taking their ideas, branding them with his.

37:50.560 --> 37:52.301
I don't know what you're talking about.

37:52.395 --> 37:54.682
Did I lose you? Did I lose you?

37:54.981 --> 37:58.565
Just talk to me like a real person.
What is it that you sell? Come on.

37:59.319 --> 38:01.060
Okay, how about this?

38:02.405 --> 38:04.316
We sell computer software.

38:04.491 --> 38:05.652
All right.

38:06.451 --> 38:07.816
My dad's dream.

38:08.828 --> 38:10.068
And he did it.

38:10.163 --> 38:13.656
Speaking of dreams,
was it your dream to be a janitor?

38:16.169 --> 38:18.001
You ask a lot of questions.

38:18.713 --> 38:21.796
I'm sorry. That's what an ass will do.

38:25.804 --> 38:27.169
You said it.

38:28.348 --> 38:31.181
No. I was in nursing school.

38:33.520 --> 38:36.387
I had two years left. I was close.

38:37.273 --> 38:39.184
Two years left? What happened?

38:40.985 --> 38:45.104
Two years ago, her dad died in Iraq.
He was in the military.

38:45.198 --> 38:48.031
So it all fell on me. I quit school.

38:49.202 --> 38:52.615
But I needed a job, so I'm a janitor.

38:54.666 --> 38:57.954
- I'm sorry.
- You know what?

38:58.044 --> 39:01.082
My boyfriend was on his way over
to help with the car

39:01.172 --> 39:03.459
and if I'm not there, or if you...

